<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>About</title>

  <style>
    body {
      font-family: "Bradley Hand", cursive;
      background: #fff8d6;
      color: #1a4b8c;
      padding: 2rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      max-width: 650px;
      margin: 0 auto;

      /* Paper texture */
      background-image:
        radial-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.03) 1px, transparent 1px),
        linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.6), rgba(255,255,255,0.6));
      background-size: 4px 4px, 100% 100%;
      position: relative;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
      color: #1a4b8c;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 2;
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 2;
    }

    /* Sticky-note Back link */
    .back-link {
      display: inline-block;
      background: #ffeeb0;
      padding: 0.7rem 1.2rem;
      border: 1px solid #d8cfa0;
      box-shadow: 3px 4px 7px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
      transform: rotate(-2deg);
      font-family: "Bradley Hand", cursive;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: #1a4b8c;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 2;
    }

    /* Seasonal doodles around Back link */
    .back-link::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      top: -22px;
      left: -28px;
      width: 190%;
      height: 190%;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at 20% 30%, rgba(255,200,230,0.35), transparent 70%), /* Spring petals */
        radial-gradient(circle at 80% 20%, rgba(255,220,140,0.35), transparent 70%), /* Summer sun */
        radial-gradient(circle at 20% 80%, rgba(210,130,70,0.35), transparent 70%),  /* Autumn leaves */
        radial-gradient(circle at 80% 80%, rgba(180,220,255,0.35), transparent 70%); /* Winter snow */
      z-index: -1;
      transform: rotate(3deg);
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    Seasonal Notes is a small, quiet experiment in noticing.
    Instead of building a traditional website with tidy pages and rigid structure,
    this project gathers fragments — small seasonal impressions — and scatters them
    across a single canvas.
  </p>

  <p>
    The notes are intentionally a little crooked, like sticky notes pinned
    to a wall or scribbles left on a desk. They aren’t meant to stand alone as
    pages. They belong together, side by side, forming a loose collage of the year.
  </p>

  <p>
    This page exists only to explain the intention behind the form — a companion
    note to the main piece, written in the margin.
  </p>

  <p>
    <a class="back-link" href="../">Back to Seasonal Notes</a>
  </p>

</body>
</html>
